In this press gaggle, Deputy Press Secretary Bill Burton provides updates on various topics. He mentions that President Obama has been informed about General Petraeus collapsing in a Senate hearing, but they have not spoken yet. Burton also discusses the progress in Afghanistan and the plan to transition forces. He addresses questions about the upcoming speech, mentioning that the President will focus on the actions taken to address the oil spill, the economic impact, and safety regulations. He also talks about the timeline for restoring the Gulf region and the trust in BP's information. Burton clarifies the importance of the flow rate in containment efforts and mentions ongoing investigations into the BP oil spill. He mentions that the President wants to ensure that BP has enough funds to compensate affected individuals. There are also questions about the escrow account and the President's awareness of death threats against Senator Kennedy. The press gaggle ends with some light-hearted banter about the oppressive heat.